        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 7:09PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 709 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles south of Clarendon, moving northwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Clarendon, Greenbelt Lake, and Lelia Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
